eries</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/11/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-texas-tech-to-open-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/11/baseball-mountaineers-defeat-texas-tech-to-open-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tyrus Hall" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/10/EKQ04283.jpeg" /><br /><br />LUBBOCK, Texas – The No. 17 West Virginia University baseball team defeated Texas Tech, 12-8, Friday night at Dan Law Field at Rip Griffin Park. The Mountaineers improve to 23-7 and 9-4 in the Big 12 while the Red Raiders fall to 19-14 and 5-8 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/10/EKQ04283.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/10/EKQ04283.jpeg"><media:title>Tyrus Hall</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/4/10/EKQ04283.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2026 00:49:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58991</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Drop Match to No. 36 Houston</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/10/tennis-mountaineers-drop-match-to-no-36-houston</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/4/10/tennis-mountaineers-drop-match-to-no-36-houston</guid><category>Tennis</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Julie Bousseau" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/4/10/WVB00208.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University tennis team (7-12, 1-11 Big 12) dropped a 4-0 decision to No. 36 Houston (17-5, 7-5 Big 1